The Randburg Magistrates&#8217; Court on Thursday postponed the case of former estate agent Vicki Momberg to allow her doctor to testify. On February 3, 2016, Momberg, 48, was caught on camera using abusive and racist language towards police officers after they tried to assist her. Momberg was visibly upset. She had been a victim of a smash-and-grab theft. She is facing four counts of crimen injuria for her alleged utterances. The matter was postponed to June 2. African News Agency (ANA) ALSO READ: &#8216;Racist&#8217; Vicki Momberg now faces 8 charges For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.